				<p>I forgot to make a Big Giant Note in the recipe about the &#8220;biscuity&#8221; and/or &#8220;baking powder-y&#8221; taste many people dislike in scones and biscuits. It comes from using a baking powder with aluminum in it, and <a href="http://smittenkitchen.com/tips/why-are-my-baked-goods-turning-blue/" rel="nofollow">it is entirely avoidable</a>.</p>
