<li class="commentbody" id="comment-435675">
			<cite>unsightly</cite>
						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-435675" title="">October 24, 2010</a> 

		
			<div class="commentcount">232</div>

				<p>I made these with double the jalapenos, and they still had NO heat. I know it wasn&#8217;t the jalapenos, as they were from my garden and I had a very spicy crop this year. I think the combination of them cooking down in the butter and then again in the oven causes most of the heat to cook out. I would try maybe just tossing them in the melted butter, but not actually cooking them before they go in the oven. Maybe also adding 1/2 tsp of cayenne. These were tasty, but I was disappointed in the lack of heat.</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
<li class="commentbody" id="comment-435881">
